From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Codex <codex@example.com>
Date: Tue, 30 Jun 2026 10:30:00 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] libxcrypt: disable werror on LoongArch64

libxcrypt 4.4.27 enables warnings-as-errors by default.  On the
LoongArch64 build host used for this adaptation, newer GCC diagnoses
lib/util-base64.c with -Wunterminated-string-initialization:

  initializer-string for array of 'unsigned char' truncates NUL terminator

That warning is in libxcrypt's bundled source and is not specific to Kong's
LoongArch64 integration.  The package's configure script already provides
--disable-werror for this compatibility case, so use that switch only for
LoongArch64 instead of patching C sources or weakening other platforms.
---
 build/cross_deps/libxcrypt/BUILD.libxcrypt.bazel | 5 +++++
 1 file changed, 5 insertions(+)

diff --git a/build/cross_deps/libxcrypt/BUILD.libxcrypt.bazel b/build/cross_deps/libxcrypt/BUILD.libxcrypt.bazel
index 1210e3f..8ae3385 100644
--- a/build/cross_deps/libxcrypt/BUILD.libxcrypt.bazel
+++ b/build/cross_deps/libxcrypt/BUILD.libxcrypt.bazel
@@ -30,6 +30,11 @@ configure_make(
             "--enable-obsolete-api=no",
         ],
         "//conditions:default": [],
+    }) + select({
+        "@kong//:loongarch64-linux": [
+            "--disable-werror",
+        ],
+        "//conditions:default": [],
     }),
     configure_xcompile = True,  # use automatic cross compile detection
     lib_source = ":all_srcs",
-- 
2.45.0
